<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi on <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE">Tuesday</TIMEX3>  <EVENT eid="e1" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">announced</EVENT> a reorganization of Forza Italia, the political party he <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">created</EVENT>  <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DURATION">five months</TIMEX3> ago which is <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE">now</TIMEX3> <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">made</EVENT> up of at least 13,000 clubs.&#13;
Berlusconi <EVENT eid="e4" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">told</EVENT> a <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">meeting</EVENT> of the Forza senators group that the founding  "coordinating committee" would be <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">enlarged</EVENT>.&#13;
It would be <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">broadened</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">include</EVENT> the heads of the party's two  parliamentary groups, he <EVENT eid="e9" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT>. Eighteen issue-based departments would also be  <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">created</EVENT>.&#13;
Thirteen out of the 18 departments would be <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">mirror</EVENT> existing parliamentary  commissions and would <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">supply</EVENT> research work to the party's deputies, Berlusconi  <EVENT eid="e13" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT>.&#13;
Gianni Pilo, a Forza deputy, <EVENT eid="e14" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">told</EVENT> AFP the objective was to "<EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">create</EVENT> an  entity the heart of which <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">works</EVENT> democratically."&#13;
The idea is "not to <EVENT eid="e17" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="NEG" modality="none">transform</EVENT> Forza Italia into a party but to <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">make</EVENT> it a  very open, supple movement."&#13;
<EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">Showing</EVENT> some splits in the ranks, however, Tiziana Parenti, a Forza MP and  candidate to the powerful parliamentary anti-Mafia committee <EVENT eid="e20" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">told</EVENT> a press  conference she <EVENT eid="e21" class="I_STATE" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">hoped</EVENT> Forza would <EVENT eid="e22" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">become</EVENT> "a structured party in order to <EVENT eid="e23" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="INFINITIVE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">obtain</EVENT>  more transparency within the democratic game."&#13;
